{"content": "Let's carefully recompute:\n\nGiven:\n\\[\nf(x) = x^7 + a x^3 + c x\n\\]\n\\[\nf(5) = 3\n\\]\nWe want \\( f(-5) \\).\n\nFirst, compute \\( f(-5) \\):\n\n\\[\nf(-5) = (-5)^7 + a(-5)^3 + c(-5)\n\\]\n\\[\n= -78125 + a(-125) + (-5)c\n\\]\n\\[\n= -78125 - 125a - 5c\n\\]\n\nRecall:\n\\[\nf(5) = 78125 + 125a + 5c = 3\n\\]\n\nSo,\n\\[\nf(-5) = -78125 - 125a - 5c\n\\]\n\nNow, let's add the two:\n\n\\[\nf(5) + f(-5) = (78125 + 125a + 5c) + (-78125 - 125a - 5c) = 0\n\\]\n\\[\nf(-5) = -f(5) = -3\n\\]\n\n**Final Answer:**\n\\[\n\\boxed{-3}\n\\]\n\nSo the correct choice is **(A) -3**.", "in": 379, "out": 261}